{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/the-major-flaw-with-data-scientists-357a7aee27db", "time": 1682995840.474524, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/the-major-flaw-with-data-scientists-357a7aee27db/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Agile (Data)Science. Can the notion of a data \u2018scientist\u2019\u2026 | by Dominik Haitz | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Agile (Data)Science", "description": "This post is about two things a (data) scientist typically comes along with: a scientific mindset, which is incredibly valuable, and an \u201cacademic working style\u201d, which can be a major handicap. A\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/top-5-mistakes-of-greenhorn-data-scientists-90fa26201d51", "anchor_text": "Generation Kaggle", "paragraph_index": 4}], "all_paragraphs": ["This post is about two things a (data) scientist typically comes along with: a scientific mindset, which is incredibly valuable, and an \u201cacademic working style\u201d, which can be a major handicap.", "A well-grounded scientific education equips a data scientist with important traits:", "As such, a data scientist\u2019s skills are immensely useful for digital businesses.", "In academia, a typical PhD thesis goes like this:", "A large portion of data science recruits have been through this process, and it has inevitably shaped their professional behavior. Something similar is true for \u201dGeneration Kaggle\u201c.", "However, the \u201cacademic working style\u201d often clashes with the requirements of today\u2019s digital economy. Especially in an agile environment, a different behavior is necessary for success:", "Of course, this doesn\u2019t mean not to double-check your results, or release head over heels. Also, there\u2019s a difference between fast-paced digital product development and e.g. working in a large company\u2019s fundamental research department.", "Personally, after transitioning from academia to industry, I had to adjust my working style i